==English==
From Greek [[παλαιοντολογία]] (''paleontologia''), from [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[παλαιός]]''' (''paleos'') "old" + '''[[όν]]''' (''on'') "being, creature" + [[[[λόγος]]]] "[[logos]]"
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''paleontology'''
#The [[study]] of the [[form]]s of [[life]] existing in [[prehistoric]] or [[geologic]] times, especially as represented by [[fossil]]s

===Etymology===
Greek ''palaios'' meaning old + Greek ''logos'' meaning the study of

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[paleontologia]]
*French: [[paléontologie]] ''f''
*Greek: [[παλαιοντολογία]] (''paleontologia'')
*Swedish: [[paleontologi]] ''c''

